UNITED STATES of America ex rel. Srul GOLDBRAND, also known as Sol. Goldbrand, Appellant, v. COMMISSIONER OF IMMIGRATION, ELLIS ISLAND, NEW YORK HARBOR, Respondent. No. 143. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Nov. 4, 1935. Tauber & Freedman, of New York City, for relator. F. W. H. Adams, U. S. Atty., of New York City (Gregory F. Noonan, Asst. U. S. Atty., of New York City, of counsel), for respondent.

Before MANTON, AUGUSTUS N. HAND, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Order affirmed.
